The '''Nothoiin Route''' was a [[Hyperspace route/Legends|hyperlane]] that connected [[Nothoiin/Legends|Nothoiin]] with [[Polmanar/Legends|Polmanar]]<ref name="Name">''[[Galactic Gazetteer: Hoth and the Greater Javin]]'' does not name this route on its map, but includes a subsection titled "Nothoiin Corridor and Route," which goes on to say, "These worlds include [[Council (planet)/Legends|Council]], Nothoiin, [[Bavva/Legends|Bavva]], and Polmanar." Council, Nothoiin, and Bavva are all seen to be on the Nothoiin Corridor on the map, but not Polmanar, meaning the Nothoiin Route is the hyperlane connecting Nothoiin and Polmanar.</ref> and the [[Lipsec Run/Legends|Lipsec Run]]. It was located within the [[Anoat sector/Legends|Anoat subsector]] of the [[Greater Javin/Legends|Greater Javin]] [[Sector/Legends|sector]].<ref name="TEA" />

[[Standard century/Legends|Centuries]] before the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], entrepreneur [[Ecclessis Figg/Legends|Ecclessis Figg]] established this trade route between the [[Planet/Legends|planets]] [[Nothoiin/Legends|Nothoiin]] and [[Isde Naha/Legends|Isde Naha]] in the [[Greater Javin]] region of the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]]. The [[Hyperspace route/Legends|route]] opened up the backwaters of what was then the [[Javin sector/Legends|Javin sector]] by forging a secondary link between the [[Corellian Trade Spine/Legends|Corellian Trade Spine]] and the [[Nothoiin Corridor]].<ref name="GG" /> The leg of this route from the [[Mev system/Legends|Mev system]] to [[Isde Naha/Legends|Isde Naha]] eventually became a part of the Lipsec Run.<ref name="TEA" />

